<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4497] Erlang records should use map() for map type</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4497</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the Thrift Erlang code generator is given the &quot;maps&quot; option, it generates records with #{} as the field type. However #{} is the type for an empty map. The Erlang &lt;a href=&quot;http://erlang.org/doc/reference_manual/typespec.html#id79546&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Types and Function Specifications&lt;/a&gt; says:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Notice that the syntactic representation of &lt;tt&gt;map()&lt;/tt&gt; is &lt;tt&gt;#{any() =&amp;gt; any()&lt;/tt&gt;} (or &lt;tt&gt;#{_ =&amp;gt; _&lt;/tt&gt;}), not #{ }. The notation #{ } specifies the singleton type for the empty map.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
